---
import LayoutEN from '../../../layouts/LayoutEN.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';

const covers = [
  { titel: 'Normale Mensen Bestaan Niet', url: 'https://open.spotify.com/show/60HbNceKiz1BJeuhVzmQMe', cover: '/images/diensten/podcast-cover-1.webp' },
  { titel: 'Uit de School', url: 'https://open.spotify.com/show/7gEsTnOwximLP7QpKVaK6D', cover: '/images/diensten/podcast-cover-7.webp' },
  { titel: 'Natuurlijk!Deelmobiliteit', url: 'https://open.spotify.com/show/0UWucGAIw9miV2azC0MYvY', cover: '/images/diensten/podcast-cover-4.webp' },
  { titel: 'Bouwverhalen', url: 'https://open.spotify.com/show/3Hqc9l6szV90EnF3vnZ4Ew', cover: '/images/diensten/podcast-cover-2.webp' },
  { titel: 'Endo Girlies', url: 'https://open.spotify.com/show/2krYyXN7BjbePOvXmw9z8a', cover: '/images/diensten/podcast-cover-3.webp' },
  { titel: 'Aan Tafel', url: 'https://open.spotify.com/show/7z88bnUTbozccCqw3Snupq', cover: '/images/diensten/podcast-cover-6.webp' },
  { titel: 'Live Above', url: 'https://open.spotify.com/show/1TKnGhZIueFPAHxct4pS9Z', cover: '/images/diensten/podcast-cover-8.webp' },
  { titel: 'Dealen met de Dood', url: 'https://open.spotify.com/show/3FaG9rbcMqqfDBuf6naAke', cover: '/images/diensten/podcast-cover-5.webp' },
];
---

<LayoutEN
  title="Podcast"
  description="Podcast production in our studio at the Grote Markt in The Hague. From concept and recording to editing and distribution. Astrolads takes care of everything, from idea to publication."
  image="/images/og/diensten/podcast.jpg"
>

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "serviceType": "Podcast production",
    "provider": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Astrolads", "@id": "https://astrolads.com/#organization" },
    "areaServed": { "@type": "Country", "name": "Netherlands" },
    "description": "Podcast production from concept to delivery. Recording in our own studio in The Hague, including editing, mixing and distribution.",
    "url": "https://astrolads.com/en/services/podcast"
  })} />

  <div class="dienst-page">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <Breadcrumb 
        lang="en"
        items={[
          { name: 'Services', url: '/en/services' },
          { name: 'Podcast' }
        ]} 
      />

      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="dienst-header">
        <div class="dienst-header-titel">
          <p class="section-label">Services</p>
          <h1>Podcast</h1>
        </div>
        <div class="dienst-header-img">
          <div class="header-slider">
            <img class="header-slide active" src="/images/diensten/podcast-slide-1.webp" alt="Astrolads podcast studio" width="640" height="480" loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" decoding="sync" />
            <img class="header-slide" src="/images/diensten/podcast-slide-2.webp" alt="Astrolads podcast recording" width="640" height="480" loading="lazy" />
            <img class="header-slide pos-top" src="/images/diensten/podcast-slide-3.webp" alt="Astrolads podcast on location" width="640" height="480" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dienst-header-tekst">
          <p class="dienst-intro">No other medium captures your audience's attention for as long as a podcast. Wrapped in entertainment, it's the ideal form for connecting on content.</p>
          <p class="dienst-intro">The main advantage of a podcast is that it fits seamlessly into the listener's lifestyle. People don't have to sit down for it or stop what they're doing. They listen while working, cooking or driving. That's why a podcast shouldn't just be about the content, but should also be an entertaining format. So you serve your audience whether they want depth or simply relaxation.</p>
          <a href="/en/contact" class="btn-orange">Get in touch</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Slider left, text right -->
      <div class="podcast-tekst-sectie">
        <div class="podcast-slider">
          <img class="podcast-slide active" src="/images/diensten/podcast-sfeer-1.webp" alt="Astrolads podcast recording" loading="lazy" />
          <img class="podcast-slide" src="/images/diensten/podcast-sfeer-2.webp" alt="Astrolads podcast studio" loading="lazy" />
          <img class="podcast-slide" src="/images/diensten/podcast-sfeer-3.webp" alt="Astrolads podcast on location" loading="lazy" />
          <img class="podcast-slide pos-top" src="/images/diensten/podcast-sfeer-4.webp" alt="Astrolads podcast on location" loading="lazy" />
          <img class="podcast-slide pos-top" src="/images/diensten/podcast-sfeer-5.webp" alt="Astrolads podcast on location" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="podcast-dots">
            <button class="podcast-dot active" data-index="0"></button>
            <button class="podcast-dot" data-index="1"></button>
            <button class="podcast-dot" data-index="2"></button>
            <button class="podcast-dot" data-index="3"></button>
            <button class="podcast-dot" data-index="4"></button>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="podcast-tekst">
          <p>Besides recording and publishing audio content, it's also possible to film the entire episodes and use them as video content. It also works great for creating vertical videos for your social media channels. Either as standalone content, or to attract new listeners.</p>
          <p>We offer two options for recording podcasts. First, at our Astrolads Studio, where everything is set up to record your podcast smoothly. From studio decor to live camera switching, anything is possible. The second option is recording on location, sometimes preferred so your guests don't have to travel far, or because the desired setting (indoor or outdoor) matches the theme of the episode.</p>
          <p>From idea to publication on all major podcast platforms, we take care of everything: the setup of your unique podcast series, cover art, script, planning, recording, editing and publication.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Covers -->
      <div class="covers-sectie">
        <h2>Our productions</h2>
        <div class="covers-grid">
          {covers.map(c => (
            <a 
              href={c.url} 
              class="cover-item" 
              target="_blank" 
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              aria-label={'Listen to ' + c.titel + ' on Spotify'}
            >
              <img src={c.cover} alt={'Podcast cover ' + c.titel + ' by Astrolads'} loading="lazy" />
              <div class="cover-overlay">
                <span class="cover-titel">{c.titel}</span>
                <span class="cover-cta">Listen →</span>
              </div>
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="dienst-cta">
        <h2>Ready to get started?</h2>
        <p>Curious what a podcast can do for your organisation? We're happy to think along with you.</p>
        <a href="/en/contact" class="btn-orange">Get in touch</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</LayoutEN>

<style>
  .dienst-page { padding: 64px 0 96px; }

  .dienst-header {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    grid-template-areas:
      "titel slider"
      "tekst slider";
    gap: 0 80px; align-items: start;
    margin-bottom: 96px;
  }
  .dienst-header-titel { grid-area: titel; align-self: end; padding-bottom: 16px; }
  .dienst-header-img { grid-area: slider; align-self: center; }
  .dienst-header-tekst { grid-area: tekst; }
  .dienst-header-titel h1 {
    font-size: clamp(40px, 5vw, 64px);
    font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  .dienst-intro {
    font-size: 17px; color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .dienst-intro + .dienst-intro { margin-top: -8px; margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .header-slider { position: relative; height: 460px; border-radius: var(--radius); overflow: hidden; }
  .header-slide {
    position: absolute; inset: 0;
    width: 100%; height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover; opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 1s ease;
  }
  .header-slide.active { opacity: 1; }
  .pos-top { object-position: center 15% !important; }

  /* Text + slider */
  .podcast-tekst-sectie {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 80px; align-items: start;
    margin-bottom: 96px;
  }
  .podcast-slider {
    position: relative; border-radius: var(--radius);
    overflow: hidden; height: 440px;
  }
  .podcast-slide {
    position: absolute; inset: 0;
    width: 100%; height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover; opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity .8s ease;
  }
  .podcast-slide.active { opacity: 1; }
  .podcast-dots {
    position: absolute; bottom: 16px; left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    display: flex; gap: 8px; z-index: 2;
  }
  .podcast-dot {
    width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,.5);
    border: none; cursor: pointer; padding: 0;
    transition: background .2s;
  }
  .podcast-dot.active { background: #fff; }
  .podcast-tekst { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 24px; }
  .podcast-tekst p { color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.9; font-size: 16px; }
  .podcast-tekst strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 700; }

  /* Covers */
  .covers-sectie { margin-bottom: 96px; }
  .covers-sectie h2 { font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 40px; text-align: center; }
  .covers-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .cover-item {
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    border-radius: 16px;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: transform .2s, box-shadow .2s;
    position: relative;
    display: block;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
  }
  .cover-item:hover { transform: translateY(-4px); box-shadow: 0 12px 32px rgba(0,0,0,.12); }
  .cover-item img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; }
  .cover-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(0,0,0,.85) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,.3) 50%, transparent 100%);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    padding: 16px;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity .25s ease;
    color: #fff;
  }
  .cover-item:hover .cover-overlay { opacity: 1; }
  .cover-item:focus-visible .cover-overlay { opacity: 1; }
  .cover-titel {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .cover-cta {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--orange);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: .05em;
  }

  /* CTA */
  .dienst-cta {
    text-align: center;
    background: var(--navy);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 64px;
    color: #fff;
  }
  .dienst-cta h2 { font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .dienst-cta p { opacity: .8; margin-bottom: 32px; font-size: 16px; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .dienst-page { padding: 32px 0 56px; }

    /* Header: title → slider → text → button */
    .dienst-header {
      display: flex !important;
      flex-direction: column !important;
      grid-template-areas: none !important;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
      gap: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 56px;
    }
    .dienst-header-titel,
    .dienst-header-img,
    .dienst-header-tekst {
      grid-area: auto !important;
      align-self: auto !important;
      width: 100%;
    }
    .dienst-header-titel {
      padding-bottom: 0;
    }
    .dienst-header-titel h1 {
      font-size: clamp(28px, 7vw, 36px);
      line-height: 1.15;
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }
    .dienst-intro {
      font-size: 14px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .dienst-intro + .dienst-intro { margin-top: -4px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
    .header-slider {
      height: auto !important;
      aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
      width: 100%;
      position: relative;
    }
    .header-slider .header-slide {
      position: absolute !important;
      inset: 0 !important;
      width: 100% !important;
      height: 100% !important;
      object-fit: cover !important;
    }

    /* Text + atmosphere slider: slider first, then text */
    .podcast-tekst-sectie {
      display: flex; flex-direction: column;
      gap: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 56px;
    }
    .podcast-tekst-sectie .podcast-slider { order: -1; }
    .podcast-slider {
      height: auto !important;
      aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
      max-height: 240px;
      width: 100%;
      position: relative;
    }
    .podcast-slider .podcast-slide {
      position: absolute !important;
      inset: 0 !important;
      width: 100% !important;
      height: 100% !important;
      object-fit: cover !important;
    }
    .podcast-dot { width: 10px; height: 10px; }
    .podcast-tekst { gap: 16px; }
    .podcast-tekst p {
      font-size: 14px;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    /* Covers: 3 columns on mobile, overlay always visible at bottom */
    .covers-sectie { margin-bottom: 56px; }
    .covers-sectie h2 {
      font-size: 24px;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }
    .covers-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 10px;
    }
    .cover-overlay {
      display: none;
    }

    /* CTA compact */
    .dienst-cta {
      padding: 36px 24px;
    }
    .dienst-cta h2 {
      font-size: 22px;
      line-height: 1.3;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }
    .dienst-cta p {
      font-size: 14px;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  var podcastSlides = document.querySelectorAll('.podcast-slide');
  var podcastDots = document.querySelectorAll('.podcast-dot');
  var podcastCurrent = 0;
  function podcastGoTo(i) {
    podcastSlides[podcastCurrent].classList.remove('active');
    podcastDots[podcastCurrent].classList.remove('active');
    podcastCurrent = i;
    podcastSlides[podcastCurrent].classList.add('active');
    podcastDots[podcastCurrent].classList.add('active');
  }
  podcastDots.forEach(function(dot) {
    dot.addEventListener('click', function() {
      podcastGoTo(parseInt(dot.getAttribute('data-index')));
    });
  });
  setInterval(function() { podcastGoTo((podcastCurrent + 1) % podcastSlides.length); }, 4000);

  var headerSlides = document.querySelectorAll('.header-slide');
  var headerCurrent = 0;
  setInterval(function() {
    headerSlides[headerCurrent].classList.remove('active');
    headerCurrent = (headerCurrent + 1) % headerSlides.length;
    headerSlides[headerCurrent].classList.add('active');
  }, 4000);
</script>